The paper focuses on the development of drawing tools for Virtual Reality (VR) and enhancing sketch-based interfaces with a supporting system for interactive model retrieval. This work involves the use of 3D models, sketching, and interaction techniques, which are commonly associated with computer graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of computer vision (cs.CV) for sketch recognition and retrieval, multimedia (cs.MM) for the use of virtual environments, and information retrieval (cs.IR) for the search and retrieval of 3D models.
